  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a sweep of the prior daily low followed by a close back inside the range, establishing bullish bias for the next day. Analyst then identified an hourly fair value gap (IRL) and equal highs (ERL) as key liquidity levels.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the daily low but closed back inside the range, signaling a potential bullish reversal; the analyst focused on the hourly FVG as internal range liquidity and equal highs as external range liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, observed that price swept the daily low and closed back inside the range, establishing a bullish bias for the following day.",
    "Step 2: Identified the hourly fair value gap (FVG) at ~67.30–67.40 as internal range liquidity (IRL) and the equal highs at ~67.54/67.53 as external range liquidity (ERL).",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 5-minute chart and looked for a change in state of delivery (CISD) using the hourly IRL-to-ERL structure; noted the initial move lacked clean down-close candles, so used the large down-close candle plus continuation as proxy for CISD.",
    "Step 4: Waited for retest of the mean threshold of the down-close series (~67.28–67.34), then identified a propulsion block forming at that zone after price swept the consolidation low.",
    "Step 5: Entered long on the 5-minute retest of the propulsion block’s mean threshold, placing stop below the swing low, targeting 2R and the ERL (equal highs)."
  ],
  "outcome": "First entry hit 2R target; continuation entry also hit TP. Price moved higher, confirming the bullish reversal and higher-low formation.",
  "lessons": "A daily low sweep with close back inside signals reversal potential; entries are highest probability when aligned with HTF bias, IRL/ERL structure, and confirmed by LTF CISD + propulsion block retest. Strong narrative justifies trading into taken liquidity if bias is robust.",
